Dialog.text: What's up?
Okay. Do you still want me to finish this array? I fabricated a shit-ton of glass.
You asked me to set up a new array.

Dialog.notes: (miyu sato) Irritated, trying to be respectful.
Dialog.text: Uh... well. Look - I have a message you left me. Seriously, I would not have made all this if you hadn't-
It doesn't matter?
I thought we were done.
I feel like you're upset with me.
What about you?
Right. I guess I'll see you later then.
Good night, Dr. Calvino.
Light field capture looks a little hot.
We've only ever had one.
I guess you forgot.
Test 23. Image sensor dynamic range.

Dialog.notes: (miyu sato) Answering sudden beeping from her Transcribe.

Dialog.text: No. Like what?
What is going on, Langly?
I guess. I don't know. I've been in the lab all day. Hang on. I'm looking now. I don't-
Dialog.notes: (miyu sato) Distantly we where the muffled "whoomp" of an explosion. Miyu jumps.

Dialog.text: Oh my god. I think we just lost two labs.
I have to go.
(Death Scream)
Dialog.notes: (miyu sato) The mimic has been shifting through the room to get closer to her. As she hangs up the TranScribe it leaps on her, kills her and multiplies.

Dialog.text: You were looking for me?
I've loaded the replacement reactor divertors on the freight lift as requested. I asked Connolly to send them down when convenient.
I filed an incident report.
So what's the problem?
The grounding resistor malfunctioned. Swap a new one and you should have your lights. Is that all?
I tried replacing the resistor yesterday.
And it just... melted into some kind of goo. Smelled like fried ass.
I need to get some sleep. My shift's over anyway. Maybe you'll have better luck.
Duncan. Access code to parts storage changed last shift. We had a short, so security came up and reset.
How's it coming?
Still not answering. What's wrong?
Dialog.notes: (Ivy Park) Beat after I don't know. Then slightly urgent, doesn't understand why Zach is taking so long

Dialog.text: Would voice samples work? TranScribe recordings?
I'll see if I can find her. Or her TranScribe. I'll check her room first.
He's... he's dead!
Anders. I tried to call security... I tried-
I said he's dead, Langely!
Okay. I'm okay. Sorry.
Anders went into the mag chamber to test one of the coils that's been flaking on us. I don't know what happened exactly - but there was a pulse. I think it cooked him in his suit.
No. Anders had the keycard.
Dr. Calvino?
You need my help.
Dialog.notes: (miyu sato) Flat. Doesn't care for him.

Dialog.text: I guess.
Besides Calvino getting stuck in microgravity? Because that's normal.
You are not putting this up anywhere. We're not supposed to be using TranScribe functionality for gaming.
Dialog.notes: (Emma Beatty) Emphasis on NOT. Sort of like a scolding big sister.

Dialog.text: Oh, god, Zach, shut up. And Elias, you better not be recording.
That's great!
Don't be such a baby. We either head through the door-
Unless you can handle the entire pack of Rat Men, oh spell-less wonder, we don't have much choice.
Elias? Sorry - Stabfellow?
Dialog.notes: (Emma Beatty) Catches herself after using his real name, corrects and calls out in her character's voice (accent of some sort?)

Dialog.text: Abigail, I'm recording this time.
Really? What did she say when you asked her to join us?
I left some Neuromods in my desk, and I'm not about to let those get sucked into space. I'll meet you at the front desk, Abigail. Good luck, Zach!
What? Spit it out.
Duncan. I don't give a shit about your pissing contest with Connolly. Take it to Brooks.
Dialog.notes: (Lan Nguyen) Tired. A little on edge.

Dialog.text: Code's embedded in this message.
Dialog.notes: (Lan Nguyen) As she's hanging up. Eye roll.

Dialog.text: What happened? You two get into a fight?
Shut up, Zach.
Officer Hayashi, Dr. Yu.
I'm ready, Dr. Yu.
Nothing will get past me.
Is there something I can help with, Dr. Yu?
Please stand away from the door, Dr. Yu.
Dialog.notes: [Tamiko Hayashi] Frantic when player messes with the door that is holding back a flood of aliens

Dialog.text: Those were not the last of the enemy. If more come, we will be ready.
Nothing to report.
All clear.
We survived. We did it. Thank you.
Captain Elazar inspired me, trained me. She was the reason I was assigned to Talos.
I owe Captain Elazar so much. Now she is gone.
Captain Elazar was a brave woman, I owe her for her trust. I will honor her memory.
More dead. More innocent blood. Our enemies will answer for it.
When will this end? What caused this?
Captain Elazar will want to speak to you. We only recently learned you were still on the station.
Dr. Yu, stand down!
I am warning you!
With the lifts working, we have a chance to retake the station. Thank you.
What are you doing? What are you?
Dr. Yu is one of them! Open fire!
Were you able to get the Eradicator turret plans?
These Eradicator turrets will be a great help. Thank you.
There was no need to open the door, Dr. Yu. We all could have died.
Is it your wish to kill us all?
Commander Dahl is not to be trusted.
If Commander Dahl is sighted, I will deal with him.
I heard Commander Dahl is dead. There has been too much death this day - but his, I do not regret.
I heard you found Chief Ilyushin and helped her. Thank you.
Dr. Igwe is blessed. It was fortunate you came along when you did.
Thank you for saving Officer Chaudhary, Dr. Yu.
She has told us of the... telepaths.
If we are trapped here, we will take them with us.
We are not trapped here with them. They are trapped here with us.
They will not defeat us. I will keep fighting until my last breath.
Just a Neuromod hangover. I feel... weird.
Are you kidding? I've always wanted to play an instrument, but never had the time...
Dialog.notes: (Skye Braxton) Slightly smiling at the 'keytar' part.

Dialog.text: I'm busy enough with the extra shifts I'm getting from Captain Marks. I don't have time for a stalker.
Uh... still nothing. Sorry.
Dialog.notes: Takes a sec... check a diagnostic screen. Shakes head

Dialog.text: It's so... it's like I can see the sheet music in my head... I feel like I've been doing this since I was seven.
Dialog.notes: As if remembering an amazing memory.

Dialog.text: Besides... you ARE going to be on stage with me, right?
Dialog.notes: Making sure Danielle's ain't gonna chicken out. Emphasis on ARE.

Dialog.text: In light of what we now know the Typhon are capable of... and not capable of... it seems prudent to revisit the project cobalt material.
The new neural structures would need to mature over a series of actual experiences.
